1
00:00:04,225 --> 00:00:06,865
From the first-class position,

2
00:00:06,865 --> 00:00:11,214
the mahā-bhāgavata
pure devotee of the Lord

3
00:00:11,214 --> 00:00:13,008
sees everything as favourable.

4
00:00:13,008 --> 00:00:14,572
“Every wave is favourable.”

5
00:00:14,572 --> 00:00:18,108
Nothing’s unfavourable to them;

6
00:00:18,169 --> 00:00:20,697
everything’s a perfect
arrangement of Kṛṣṇa.

7
00:00:20,928 --> 00:00:23,671
[Devotee: The Key to Kṛṣṇa Consciousness]

8
00:00:24,025 --> 00:00:34,697
So they cannot be brought down
by bad association or any circumstance.

9
00:00:34,724 --> 00:00:37,481
And the third-class position,

10
00:00:37,481 --> 00:00:40,982
they more or less think that
everything is unfavourable.

11
00:00:40,982 --> 00:00:49,033
Their focus is very narrow,
sometimes to the exclusion of devotees.

12
00:00:49,033 --> 00:00:56,224
They go, “Let me worship my God,”
and they can’t deal with anybody else.

13
00:00:56,224 --> 00:01:05,898
It means it’s a potentially faulty position,

14
00:01:05,898 --> 00:01:16,064
because it leads one to not properly
respect who devotees are,

15
00:01:16,064 --> 00:01:22,025
and devotees are the key
to Kṛṣṇa consciousness.

16
00:01:22,025 --> 00:01:28,231
This is a religion where the emphasis is
put on the devotee more than the Lord.

17
00:01:28,231 --> 00:01:33,625
That’s what distinguishes
Kṛṣṇa consciousness from other …

18
00:01:33,625 --> 00:01:40,480
it’s one of the distinguishing factors
between this and other theistic systems.

19
00:01:40,480 --> 00:01:46,025
The maximum amount of emphasis
put on the devotee of the Lord,

20
00:01:46,025 --> 00:01:52,544
and the devotee of the Lord
as the agent of the Lord;

21
00:01:52,544 --> 00:01:55,650
that through the devotee
you get a substantial connection.

22
00:01:55,650 --> 00:02:01,185
So for those who are seriously
pursuing spiritual life,

23
00:02:01,185 --> 00:02:04,982
they put themselves under the guidance
of a qualified Vaiṣnava

24
00:02:04,982 --> 00:02:07,264
and follow their direction.

25
00:02:07,264 --> 00:02:09,148
Because admittedly they’ll say,

26
00:02:09,148 --> 00:02:16,703
“I have no standard which
to make these judgements by.”

27
00:02:16,703 --> 00:02:20,149
So we’re told,
“Develop dharma-buddhi.”

28
00:02:20,149 --> 00:02:24,273
Where do you get it from?
Sādhu, Śāstra, Guru, Vaiṣnava.

29
00:02:24,273 --> 00:02:27,518
‘Sādhu-sańga’, ‘sādhu-sańga’
—sarva-śāstre kaya

30
00:02:27,518 --> 00:02:30,771
lava-mātra sādhu-saṅge
sarva-siddhi haya (Cc: Madhya, 2.22.131);

31
00:02:30,771 --> 00:02:34,024
through sādhau saṅgaḥ svato vare,

32
00:02:34,024 --> 00:02:36,816
through superior association

33
00:02:36,816 --> 00:02:45,816
you will acquire
superior assessment ability.

34
00:02:45,816 --> 00:02:47,464
It’s like anything.

35
00:02:47,464 --> 00:02:52,024
Your judgement faculty 
will improve

36
00:02:52,024 --> 00:02:55,705
under the influence of
Sādhu, Śāstra, Guru, and Vaiṣnava,

37
00:02:55,705 --> 00:02:58,899
if that’s what it is. Not other things.

38
00:02:58,899 --> 00:03:01,905
So that’s why we have to become
acquainted with those things,

39
00:03:01,905 --> 00:03:05,342
or minimally, at least put ourselves
under the guidance

40
00:03:05,342 --> 00:03:08,317
of someone who is
acquainted with such things.

